        "Life cycle annotation drill: draw a blank two-circle Plasmodium life cycle template (human circle, mosquito circle). Without reference, fill in every stage name, the type of reproduction at each stage, and the cell type invaded. Check against your annotated diagram. For every stage you miss or misplace, redraw that section of the cycle three times immediately.",
        "Pathogen identification drill: write twelve protist names on separate slips of paper. Draw one at random. Within 90 seconds, write: disease, transmission route, vector (if any), supergroup, unique cellular feature, treatment. Score 1 point per correct field (maximum 6 per round). Target: 60/60 across 10 rounds before any pathology exam.",
