        "Structural abnormality scenario: given a description such as 'a phenotypically normal woman with 45 chromosomes whose child has Down syndrome with 46 chromosomes', identify the structural abnormality type, write the parental and child karyotypes, explain the meiotic segregation mechanism, and estimate recurrence risk. Practise with five different scenarios covering Robertsonian translocation, pericentric inversion, and reciprocal translocation carriers."
