                "Create an epistasis comparison table — rows: recessive epistasis, dominant epistasis, duplicate recessive epistasis, complementary genes; columns: (1) which genotype class is epistatic; (2) standard 9:3:3:1 classes that merge; (3) modified ratio; (4) molecular explanation; (5) specific organism example. Build this from the 9:3:3:1 base in every row — never just write the ratio from memory.",
                "Create a Mendel's laws comparison table: Law of Segregation vs Law of Independent Assortment — columns: (1) what separates; (2) when during meiosis; (3) experimental evidence (cross type and expected ratio); (4) modern mechanistic understanding; (5) when the law does NOT apply (limitation). This table must distinguish the two laws precisely — many students conflate them.",
                "Create an ABO blood group complete genotype-phenotype table: rows for all six possible genotypes (I^A I^A, I^A i, I^B I^B, I^B i, I^A I^B, ii); columns: (1) blood type; (2) antigens on red blood cells; (3) antibodies in plasma; (4) can receive from; (5) can donate to. Include the universal donor and universal recipient designations and their limitations."
