                "Dissect the 9:3:3:1 dihybrid ratio from first principles: (1) identify that AaBb produces four gamete types each at 1/4 frequency; (2) construct a 4×4 grid and fill all 16 cells; (3) categorise each cell by phenotypic class (A_B_, A_bb, aaB_, aabb); (4) count each class; (5) confirm 9+3+3+1=16. Then use the product rule to re-derive: P(A_) = 3/4, P(B_) = 3/4, P(A_B_) = 9/16. Confirm these give the same result.",
                "Dissect a published pedigree of Huntington's disease: (a) identify all affected individuals and mark them; (b) note that the trait appears in every generation — name which pattern this suggests; (c) identify any mating between an affected and unaffected individual and count affected and unaffected offspring; (d) confirm the pattern is consistent with autosomal dominant; (e) assign genotypes to every individual in the pedigree; (f) calculate the probability that an unborn child of an affected individual will be affected.",
