        "Dissect conditional probability in genetics: given that a couple are both obligate carriers (Aa × Aa) and have had one unaffected child, calculate the probability that the unaffected child is a carrier. Set up as: P(carrier | unaffected) = P(carrier AND unaffected) / P(unaffected) = (1/2) / (3/4) = 2/3. Verify using the Punnett square: of the three unaffected outcomes (AA, Aa, Aa), two are carriers. Connect this to clinical genetic counselling practice.",
